function clean_column(col)
    return replace(lowercase(strip(col)), r"[\s-]" => "_")
end
```

The `clean_column` function first strips any leading or trailing whitespaces from the column name using the `strip` function. It then converts the column name to lowercase using the `lowercase` function. Finally, it replaces any spaces or hyphens with underscores using the `replace` function with a regular expression that matches spaces and hyphens (`r"[\s-]"`).
